    {
      "id": "2pX_bH6gT64bKAzBf2gWK",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1342.1880260678067,
      "y": 75150.37276254661,
      "width": 1100,
      "height": 675,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "#ffc9c9",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "btB",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 340267638,
      "version": 1034,
      "versionNonce": 1804796302,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1777689094442,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1.Euclidean Distance -> Measures the straight line ruler distance between two, it cares about the\nmagnitude of the difference.\n\n2 Cosine Distance -> measures the angle between two vectors, it cares about the orientation or\ndirection not the magnitude.\n\n\nEuclidian Formula ->\n    for two vector1 A = (a1, a2, a3, ....) and B = (b1, b2, b3, ....bn) the euclidian distance\n    d(A, B) = sqrt((a1-b1)^2 + (a2-b2)^2 + (a3-b3)^2 + ....)\n\nCosine formula ->\n    cosine similarity(A, B) =  (A.B)/(||A||*||B||)\n\n    A.B is the dot product of the vectors -> (a1*b1 + a2*b2 + a3*b3 + ....)\n    ||A|| is the magnitude (or L2 norm) of vector A  (sqrt(a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + ...))\n\nwe generally use cosine formula due to it is better. and its trying to find nearest based on context\non the other part euclidian is trying to find distance.\n\n\nwe store these vectors in Vector DB.\n\n\n\n\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1.Euclidean Distance -> Measures the straight line ruler distance between two, it cares about the\nmagnitude of the difference.\n\n2 Cosine Distance -> measures the angle between two vectors, it cares about the orientation or\ndirection not the magnitude.\n\n\nEuclidian Formula ->\n    for two vector1 A = (a1, a2, a3, ....) and B = (b1, b2, b3, ....bn) the euclidian distance\n    d(A, B) = sqrt((a1-b1)^2 + (a2-b2)^2 + (a3-b3)^2 + ....)\n\nCosine formula ->\n    cosine similarity(A, B) =  (A.B)/(||A||*||B||)\n\n    A.B is the dot product of the vectors -> (a1*b1 + a2*b2 + a3*b3 + ....)\n    ||A|| is the magnitude (or L2 norm) of vector A  (sqrt(a1^2 + a2^2 + a3^2 + ...))\n\nwe generally use cosine formula due to it is better. and its trying to find nearest based on context\non the other part euclidian is trying to find distance.\n\n\nwe store these vectors in Vector DB.\n\n\n\n\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
