    {
      "id": "BMF-L37WVAo-v3DrVfYD7",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1283.5563976421818,
      "y": 78211.22353428525,
      "width": 759,
      "height": 25,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bum",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 628640850,
      "version": 7,
      "versionNonce": 1054510478,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777690980246,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Second Method:  The Decision Tree Method (Binary Space Partitioning) ",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Second Method:  The Decision Tree Method (Binary Space Partitioning) ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "_rZ99KH8WNyA3PBgEVtKr",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1309.7721748847243,
      "y": 78249.77204193744,
      "width": 1012,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bun",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1112424466,
      "version": 67,
      "versionNonce": 1221904530,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777691053270,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": " if we just took the whole space and chopped it in half? \nAnd then chopped those halves in half? And so on.\n\nFirst Split: We pick a dimension (e.g., the x-axis) and find the middle point (the median). \nWe draw a vertical line there. All points to the left go into the \"left\" branch of our tree,\nand all points to the right go into the \"right\" branch.\n\nSecond Split: Now we look at the two new groups. For each group, we pick the other \ndimension (the y-axis) and split it in half with a horizontal line.\n\nKeep Splitting: We keep repeating this process, alternating which dimension we split on,\n until we only have a few points left in each final, tiny rectangle.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": " if we just took the whole space and chopped it in half? \nAnd then chopped those halves in half? And so on.\n\nFirst Split: We pick a dimension (e.g., the x-axis) and find the middle point (the median). \nWe draw a vertical line there. All points to the left go into the \"left\" branch of our tree,\nand all points to the right go into the \"right\" branch.\n\nSecond Split: Now we look at the two new groups. For each group, we pick the other \ndimension (the y-axis) and split it in half with a horizontal line.\n\nKeep Splitting: We keep repeating this process, alternating which dimension we split on,\n until we only have a few points left in each final, tiny rectangle.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
