      "text": "Q = [1.5, 2.1, 0.8, 3.9, 8.1, 7.9, 9.0, 6.6, 4.8, 5.2, 4.1, 5.0, 9.5, 8.3, 7.9, 9.1]\n\nSplit Q into chunks, just like we did for V:\n\nq_chunk1 = [1.5, 2.1, 0.8, 3.9]\nq_chunk2 = [8.1, 7.9, 9.0, 6.6]\nq_chunk3 = [4.8, 5.2, 4.1, 5.0]\nq_chunk4 = [9.5, 8.3, 7.9, 9.1]\n\nv1 = [10,23,123,16]\ndist => 1.3 +6.1+ 1.5+9.1 = 18\n\n\n\n\n Build the Distance Look-up Tables\n\nFor Chunk 1: We calculate the squared Euclidean distance from q_chunk1 to every single one of the 256 centroids in Codebook 1.\ndist_table1[0] = distance(q_chunk1, Codebook1_centroid0)²\ndist_table1[1] = distance(q_chunk1, Codebook1_centroid1)²\n...\ndist_table1[255] = distance(q_chunk1, Codebook1_centroid255)²\nFor Chunk 2: We do the same, comparing q_chunk2 to every centroid in Codebook 2, creating dist_table2.\nFor Chunk 3 & 4: We repeat the process to create dist_table3 and dist_table4.\nResult: We now have 4 tables, each with 256 pre-calculated squared distance values. \nThis took 4 * 256 = 1024 distance calculations in total.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Q = [1.5, 2.1, 0.8, 3.9, 8.1, 7.9, 9.0, 6.6, 4.8, 5.2, 4.1, 5.0, 9.5, 8.3, 7.9, 9.1]\n\nSplit Q into chunks, just like we did for V:\n\nq_chunk1 = [1.5, 2.1, 0.8, 3.9]\nq_chunk2 = [8.1, 7.9, 9.0, 6.6]\nq_chunk3 = [4.8, 5.2, 4.1, 5.0]\nq_chunk4 = [9.5, 8.3, 7.9, 9.1]\n\nv1 = [10,23,123,16]\ndist => 1.3 +6.1+ 1.5+9.1 = 18\n\n\n\n\n Build the Distance Look-up Tables\n\nFor Chunk 1: We calculate the squared Euclidean distance from q_chunk1 to every single one of the 256 centroids in Codebook 1.\ndist_table1[0] = distance(q_chunk1, Codebook1_centroid0)²\ndist_table1[1] = distance(q_chunk1, Codebook1_centroid1)²\n...\ndist_table1[255] = distance(q_chunk1, Codebook1_centroid255)²\nFor Chunk 2: We do the same, comparing q_chunk2 to every centroid in Codebook 2, creating dist_table2.\nFor Chunk 3 & 4: We repeat the process to create dist_table3 and dist_table4.\nResult: We now have 4 tables, each with 256 pre-calculated squared distance values. \nThis took 4 * 256 = 1024 distance calculations in total.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
