      "updated": 1777697564531,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Which Method is \"Best\"? A Comparison\nLet's compare the methods we've discussed across the three critical dimensions.\nMethod                 Speed (Query Latency)        Accuracy (Recall)        Memory Usage\nHNSW                          Highest                         Highest                 Highest\nIVFPQ (Hybrid)               High                      High (with re-ranking)        Lowest by Far\nIVF (Standalone)            Medium                           Medium                    Low\nTrees (e.g., KD-Tree)        Low (in high dimensions)        Low                   Medium",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Which Method is \"Best\"? A Comparison\nLet's compare the methods we've discussed across the three critical dimensions.\nMethod                 Speed (Query Latency)        Accuracy (Recall)        Memory Usage\nHNSW                          Highest                         Highest                 Highest\nIVFPQ (Hybrid)               High                      High (with re-ranking)        Lowest by Far\nIVF (Standalone)            Medium                           Medium                    Low\nTrees (e.g., KD-Tree)        Low (in high dimensions)        Low                   Medium",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "2SXhjrLlCN2LaWSdbDJu6",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1270.2721697120985,
      "y": 82364.5009120219,
      "width": 1595,
      "height": 475,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#2f9e44",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "byO",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1615018318,
      "version": 3,
      "versionNonce": 702993422,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1777698536487,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Database / Library        Category        Key Feature / Philosophy                    Primary Indexing Technique(s) Used\nMilvus                         Native          Open-source, highly scalable, \n                                                 MLOps-focused. Decoupled \n                                                       storage & compute.                      Highly Flexible: HNSW, IVFPQ, IVFFlat, and others.\nPinecone                       Native           Managed service (SaaS), \n                                                ease of use, performance-focused.             HNSW\nWeaviate                    Native           Open-source, GraphQL API, connects \n                                                   vectors in a knowledge graph.                HNSW\nQdrant                       Native          Open-source, performance-focused with \n                                                 advanced filtering. Written in Rust.            HNSW with custom quantization.\nPostgreSQL (pgvector)    Integrated        Keep your structured data and \n                                                 vectors together in a trusted relational DB.     IVFFlat and HNSW\nElasticsearch               Integrated        Combine traditional keyword search with \n                                                     semantic vector search in one query.              HNSW\nRedis                        Integrated        In-memory speed, combining vector search \n                                                    with other Redis data structures.                  HNSW\nFaiss (by Meta)        Library        The foundational C++/Python toolkit. Not a DB,\n                                                    but powers many others.                            The Reference: HNSW, IVFPQ, and many more.\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 8,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Database / Library        Category        Key Feature / Philosophy                    Primary Indexing Technique(s) Used\nMilvus                         Native          Open-source, highly scalable, \n                                                 MLOps-focused. Decoupled \n                                                       storage & compute.                      Highly Flexible: HNSW, IVFPQ, IVFFlat, and others.\nPinecone                       Native           Managed service (SaaS), \n                                                ease of use, performance-focused.             HNSW\nWeaviate                    Native           Open-source, GraphQL API, connects \n                                                   vectors in a knowledge graph.                HNSW\nQdrant                       Native          Open-source, performance-focused with \n                                                 advanced filtering. Written in Rust.            HNSW with custom quantization.\nPostgreSQL (pgvector)    Integrated        Keep your structured data and \n                                                 vectors together in a trusted relational DB.     IVFFlat and HNSW\nElasticsearch               Integrated        Combine traditional keyword search with \n                                                     semantic vector search in one query.              HNSW\nRedis                        Integrated        In-memory speed, combining vector search \n                                                    with other Redis data structures.                  HNSW\nFaiss (by Meta)        Library        The foundational C++/Python toolkit. Not a DB,\n                                                    but powers many others.                            The Reference: HNSW, IVFPQ, and many more.\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
